The paper deals with achieving Byzantine consensus in synchronous networks, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC). The networks are represented as directed graphs, which suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of network architecture and protocols (cs.NI). The paper also presents a new algorithm for achieving Byzantine consensus, which could be considered as a contribution to the field of algorithms and data structures (cs.SI). The topic of fault tolerance in networks is also relevant to the area of dependable and secure computing (cs.DSN). Finally, the paper deals with achieving consensus in networks, which is a topic related to systems and control (cs.SY).
